Installation:

    git clone http://github.com/sylvesterink/dotvim.git ~/.vim
    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

Create symlink:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    
    (If using a .gvimrc, which isn't available yet)
    ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Create directories for backup/temp files in home directory

    mkdir ~/.vimbackup
    mkdir ~/.vimtmp

To Get Updates
    git pull

To Get Submodule Updates (may be incorrect, check git submodule pull)
    cd ~/.vim/bundle/[SUBMODULE]
    git pull

ON WINDOWS
    Install it to the home directory, which can be found via the command
    :echo $HOME

    copy the vimrc to home as _vimrc
    make directories vimbackup and vimtmp in home
